      <h3 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;color:#1E293B;margin:20px 0 8px">What is a Cookie?</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom:16px">A cookie is a small file stored in your browser that websites use to remember information about you. Many websites use cookies to track you across the internet for advertising purposes. StudyBuddy does not do this.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;color:#1E293B;margin:20px 0 8px">What We Use Instead: LocalStorage</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom:8px">StudyBuddy uses your browser's <strong>localStorage</strong> — a built-in feature that saves data on your device only. It works similarly to cookies but the data never leaves your browser.</p>
      <p style="margin-bottom:8px">We store the following in localStorage:</p>

